</span></span></span><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span lang="en-GB">under</span></span><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="letter-spacing: 4.0pt;"><span lang="en-GB">
</span></span></span><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span lang="en-GB">the</span></span><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="letter-spacing: 4.0pt;"><span lang="en-GB">
</span></span></span><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span lang="en-GB">name</span></span><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="letter-spacing: 4.0pt;"><span lang="en-GB">
</span></span></span><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span lang="en-GB">of</span></span><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="letter-spacing: 4.0pt;"><span lang="en-GB">
</span></span></span><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span lang="en-GB">"urban
transformation" aiming at the interests of those in power, with
buildings built at gigantic heights, are trying to dampen the
reactions of the people by shedding crocodile tears after the
disasters.</span></span></p>
<p class="western" lang="de-DE" style="margin-left: 0cm; margin-top: 0.21cm; text-indent: 0cm;">
<span style="font-size: x-small;"><span lang="en-GB">But</span></span><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="letter-spacing: 1.5pt;"><span lang="en-GB">
</span></span></span><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span lang="en-GB">in</span></span><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="letter-spacing: 1.5pt;"><span lang="en-GB">
